ad_creative_body: If you’re tired of Mitch McConnell’s broken Washington, then I need you on this team. Join me, and let’s take our government back.
Just imagine: a Senate that works for US again. That’s a Senate without Mitch McConnell. Join Team McGrath and let’s defeat him in 2020.

This is UNDEMOCRATIC. The lack of international media coverage and the lack of social media coverage of atrocities occurring in Indonesian-occupied West Papua, is a direct result of the Indonesian government strategically preventing the world from viewing their disturbing operations on the ground. Over this past weekend, 43 students in a dormitory in Surabaya were arrested by Indonesian forces after allegations that they threw an Indonesian flag in a sewer. After their arrests, mobs of Indonesians began to form chanting racist slurs and threatening to kill Papuans. West Papuans do not find the Indonesian flag to be representative of them as a nation. West Papuans can face up to 15 years of imprisonment for raising their Morning Star Flag, which represents the nation and people of West Papua. They have long called for indpendence from Indonesia. Their lands have been subjected to mining by multinational corporations in collusion with the Indonesian government-without consultation. Over the past few decades it is estimated that over 500,000 indigenous West Papuans have been slain by the Indonesian government on their indigenous lands. #FreeWestPapua #PapuaExit #TurnitBackOn #WestPapua #Amazon #Genocide @papuaexit @freewestpapua.australia @freewestpapuacampaign @freewestpapua @shaunking

At least 22 foreign powers have spent money at Trump-owned properties to curry favor with the administration. Instead of divesting his business holdings, Trump has retained control of his family company and profited from foreign and domestic government spending at Trump properties. 

Trump and his family are using their government positions to funnel foreign cash into their pockets. It’s unethical, and it’s illegal. Add your name to tell Congress: No one is above the law.

Trump has spent nearly 300 days of his presidency at his golf courses and other properties. Each Secret Service member required to accompany him puts thousands in taxpayer dollars right into Trump’s pockets.

Trump’s frequent trips to his own properties not only pour your hard-earned tax dollars into his hands, but encourage wealthy individuals and foreign governments to visit them too. Ivanka Trump and Jared Kushner’s government positions also encourage influence-buying at the Trump properties they profit from and their businesses. Enough is enough.

Multiple lawsuits have been brought against Trump for violating the Emoluments Clause of the Constitution, which prohibits presidents from using their office to profit from foreign and state governments. Congress must also continue to investigate his violations. Add your name to tell Congress to hold Trump accountable for his corruption.

Multiple lawsuits have been brought against Trump for violating the Constitution. His presidential visits to his own properties have encouraged foreign governments to book stays at his properties as well, funnelling millions of dollars into his pocket. Receiving gifts or bribes from foreign governments is illegal.

Congress must hold Trump accountable for his corruption—from the nepotism of appointing his daughter and son-in-law to government positions, to his foreign entanglements. Tell Congress: No one is above the law, not even the president.
